  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "Dropping off a U-Haul at a different location typically involves a few simple steps. Here's a general guide:\n\n1. **Check Your Agreement**: Before you pick up the U-Haul, make sure your rental agreement allows for a different drop-off location. This should be specified during the booking process.\n\n2. **Locate the Drop-Off Site**: Use the U-Haul website or mobile app to find the nearest drop-off location that accepts returns. You can also contact U-Haul customer service for assistance.\n\n3. **Prepare for Drop-Off**: Before arriving at the drop-off location, make sure to:\n   - Remove all personal items from the truck or trailer.\n   - Clean out any debris or excess dirt.\n   - Note the fuel level; you may need to refill it to the level specified in your rental agreement.\n\n4. **Arrive at the Location**: Drive to the drop-off location and follow any signs or instructions regarding where to park the vehicle.\n\n5. **Return Process**:\n   - If the location has an attendant, they will assist you with the return.\n   - If it\u2019s a self-service drop-off, you may need to follow specific instructions outlined on signage or provided at the time of your rental. This often includes returning the keys and possibly completing a return form online.\n\n6. **Complete the Return**: Once you drop off the U-Haul, make sure to retain any documentation or confirmation emails related to the return for your records.\n\n7. **Final Inspection**: U-Haul typically conducts a quick inspection of the vehicle. If there are any issues or damages, be prepared to discuss them with the representative.\n\n8. **Billing**: After the drop-off, check your account or the U-Haul website to ensure the final charges match your rental agreement.\n\nIf you have any specific questions or if your situation is unique, it\u2019s always a good idea to reach out directly to U-Haul customer service for assistance.",
